main event: A civilian in Denville, N.J. reported a ground-visual UFO observation on 3-12-59 at 0130Z, with a duration of 0.5 minutes involving one object. The report notes that photographic evidence was discharged when sensor film was developed.
interesting points: The report suggests that the observation was real, but it was also concluded to be definitely a balloon, possibly a satellite, or an unknown phenomenon.
There was no photographic evidence available despite the presence of sensor film.

The handwritten text on the document mentions 'triolede' and 'megasite' in the first page, and 'picture' and 'negative' on the second page, which could be interpreted as cryptic references to the observed object.
The report raises questions about the nature of the 'megasite' and 'negative' mentioned in the handwritten text.
The document does not include any photographs, despite indicating the discharge of the sensor film.
